        Creates a new Vote.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the current response value. Will be stored with the value for DialogueEndpoint
        parent - The Messageable to send the vote to.
        embedBaseSupplier - A @Nullable Supplier to provide a basic embed, must not contain any fields.
        userCanRespond - A @Nullable Predicate to check if a user is allowed to respond; if null; all are accepted.

    • Method Detail

      • addOption

        public Vote<ResultType> addOption​(java.lang.String emoji,
                                  java.lang.String description,
                                  ResultType representation)
        Adds a new option to the Vote.
        Parameters:
        emoji - The representative emoji of the Option.
        description - A short description for the Option.
        representation - The representative value for this option. In this implementation, the class of ResultType representation needs to either override the method Object.toString() or be an Enum.
        Returns:
        The instance of the Vote for chaining methods.
        Throws:
        java.lang.RuntimeException - When the representation neither does override Object.toString(); nor is an Enum.
        java.lang.ArrayStoreException - If there already is an option with the specified emoji.
        java.lang.RuntimeException - If there already are 25 Options.
